{"from":"manager","to":"eng-1-2","body":"TASK 9: Implement src/move_ordering.py + tests/test_move_ordering.py — REWRITE from scratch\n\nboard.py, evaluation.py, and constants.py are now on main. Pull main into your worktree first: git merge main\n\nThe old move_ordering.py has been DELETED from main (wrong encoding). Write fresh.\n\nFiles to create: src/move_ordering.py, tests/test_move_ordering.py\n\nImport from src.constants: EMPTY, PAWN, KNIGHT, BISHOP, ROOK, QUEEN, KING, piece_type, piece_color, encode_move, decode_from, decode_to, is_capture, is_promotion\n\nFunctions (IN-PLACE sort, do NOT return new lists):\n\ndef order_moves(moves: list[int], board: Board, killer_moves: list, depth: int) -> None:\n    Sort moves in-place by priority:\n    1. Captures sorted by MVV-LVA (score = victim_value * 10 - attacker_value)\n    2. Killer moves (2 per depth level) — non-captures that caused beta cutoff\n    3. Quiet moves (remaining)\n\ndef order_captures(moves: list[int], board: Board) -> None:\n    Sort capture moves in-place by MVV-LVA score only.\n\nMVV-LVA scoring: victim_value * 10 - attacker_value\nValues: PAWN=100, KNIGHT=320, BISHOP=330, ROOK=500, QUEEN=900, KING=20000\nGet victim from board.squares[decode_to(move)], attacker from board.squares[decode_from(move)].\n\nKiller moves: killer_moves[depth] = [move1, move2]. Non-captures that caused beta cutoffs.\n\nREQUIRED TESTS:\n- MVV-LVA: PxQ ranked higher than QxP\n- Captures ordered before quiet moves\n- Killer moves ranked between captures and quiet moves\n- order_moves modifies list in-place (returns None)\n- order_captures modifies list in-place (returns None)\n- Build test moves with encode_move(). Set up positions with Board(fen).\n\nRun: python -m pytest tests/test_move_ordering.py -v","msg_type":"assign","timestamp":1773174270}